“We all need to have a fair chance to do what we want to do. How you live, how you love, what you want to believe. That’s how I want to be seen.”

"We're not a monolithic group. If I don't tell you my story, how would you know that I didn't share the experiences of the other Black people here?"

Edna, member of the Ga tribe of Ghana and Starbucks legal practice assistant, takes pride in her story and identity.pic.twitter.com/6sNZVMcKOe

“I know there are a lot of people like me out there. I can use my story and my store and my resources, and show them the pathway forward and help advance their growth and development.”

Freshness 

Store your coffee beans in an airtight container in a cool, dry place for up to a week. Never store your coffee in the freezer. 

If possible, grind right before using.

Water 

Heat water to just before boiling to bring out the full flavor of the coffee. 

For best results, use filtered water.

Grind  

A coarse grind looks like sea salt, while a fine grind resembles sugar.

Not sure which grind to use? As a general rule, the shorter the brew time, the finer the grind.

Proportion  

For the best cup of coffee, measure 2tbsp (10g) of ground coffee per 6oz water. 

That ratio too strong for your taste? Add hot water to your coffee after brewing rather than using less coffee to avoid it tasting bitter.

If you find you’re making more coffee at home these days, it’s a good time to refresh your knowledge of the four fundamentals of coffee:

 Proportion
 Grind 
 Water 
 Freshness
